The paper deals with the problem of high-dimensional convexity testing, which involves testing whether a set is convex or $\varepsilon$-far from every convex body with respect to the standard multivariate normal distribution. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper proposes sample-based testing algorithms and provides sample complexity upper and lower bounds, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these areas.
